<taxonomicName authority="Wu &amp; Hwang &amp; Lin, 2008" authorityName="Wu &amp; Hwang &amp; Lin" authorityYear="2008" box="[566,824,1744,1763]" class="Gastropoda" family="Camaenidae" genus="Satsuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="37" pageNumber="474" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="katipolensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[566,824,1744,1763]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="474">Satsuma katipolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[838,932,1744,1763]" pageId="37" pageNumber="474" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(paratype, TMMT 0679). A, whole genitalia; B, interior of genitalia. Scale bar = 5 mm. See text for abbreviations.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="38.[144,759,198,495]" box="[144,245,198,219]" pageId="38" pageNumber="475">
<emphasis box="[144,245,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="475">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[144,759,198,495]" pageId="38" pageNumber="475">
Inhabiting from 
<quantity box="[353,468,228,250]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="38" pageNumber="475" unit="m" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">
2 to 
<specimenCount box="[423,468,228,250]" pageId="38" pageNumber="475" type="generic">5 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. Adults were found in autumn (
<figureCitation box="[252,353,259,281]" captionStart="Figure 27" captionStartId="36.[144,223,741,760]" captionTargetBox="[367,1199,197,711]" captionTargetId="figure-408@36.[367,1199,197,711]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="Figure 27. Satsuma katipolensis sp. nov. A–D, holotype (TMMT 0607, shell height = 18.2 mm). E, F, paratype (TMMT 0638, shell height = 16.1 mm). G, living specimen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5446758" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5446758/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="475">Fig. 27G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[144,759,198,495]" pageId="38" pageNumber="475">
This species is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wu &amp; Hwang &amp; Lin" authorityYear="2008" box="[653,759,290,311]" class="Gastropoda" family="Camaenidae" genus="Satsuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="38" pageNumber="475" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="huberi">
<emphasis box="[653,759,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="475">S. huberi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be distinguished by the following characteristics: (1) the shell is thinner, (2) the shell colour is never ivory-white, (3) the base of the bursa stalk is expanded, (4) the base of the flagellum is more swollen, (5) the vagina is shorter than the penis and (6) the penial caecum is short.
</paragraph>
